President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Major General Robert A. Harding, U.S. Army (Retired), as the Assistant Secretary for the Department of Homeland Security (Transportation Security Administration). Obama believes that Harding's talent and expertise will make him a tremendous asset in efforts to bolster security and screening measures at airports. Harding has over 35 years of experience in the Intelligence Community, both in the military and private sectors. He served as CEO of Harding Security Associates, a company he founded, and has held various command and staff positions in the US Army. Harding's civilian education includes a Bachelor of Science degree in Business Administration, a Master of Science in Business, and a Master of Arts degree in National Security and Strategy. He has received several awards for his service, including the Defense Distinguished Service Medal and the Army Distinguished Service Medal.